{"word":"θηρεύω","slug":"θηρεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θηρεύω</b></el> <el>(θηρεύω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:θηράω'><el>θηράω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to hunt, go hunting</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to hunt after, chase, catch</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—of men, <i>to hunt down</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <i>to lay wait for</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be hunted</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: to be caught, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to hunt after</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}